This paper deals with computer vision tasks such as semantic and instance segmentation, which are typically studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses weakly supervised learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of image-level tags, which are often studied in natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents results on Cityscapes dataset, which is a popular dataset for multimodal learning (cs.MM) research.
